HEADWORD: Chank
<hw>Chank"</hw> <pr>(ch⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>⟦cced⟧a⟦ndot⟧kha</ets>. See <er>Conch</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The East Indian name for the large spiral shell
of several species of sea conch much used in making bangles, esp.
<spn>Turbinella pyrum</spn>. Called also <altname>chank
shell</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

